text: Ok cool

heard back from Aaron Cain. He says he's willing to deal with third party resellers, but in the past they've always wanted 40-60% off his listed price which makes it not worth the cost of labor for him. If we treat him as a kinda break-even product that gets people onto the shop page we could probably offer him a much better deal than that.

Shipping from him for an individual box is around $6, probably less if we got several at a time. Labor cost is harder to quantify, and depends a little on how much we pay whoever we end up hiring. So I figure best guess if we ask for about 10-15% we're at least not losing too much money. The question is basically whether it's worth including them in stock if we're not making money on them-- what do you think?
Im wondering if we can just set up an affiliate style thing
Where we pass on the order, he makes it then delivers it all himself
No labor on our part
We take 8%
Seems (to me who doesn't know shit) like an affiliate link is way more ROI. Minimal time/work for a nice cut. It wouldn't shock me to see him get a really large chunk of orders from it too.
That does sound way better
See this is why I ask you guys stuff

ok, so Aaron is on board with the 8% idea but with the following concern:

"That sounds much better than taking a huge hit on costs! There is one concern, I am constantly selling pre-made stuff off of my site as well. What I can't do is make a bunch of boxes and separate them in two groups. (Boxes I make for my site and boxes I make for your site) If I have a box to sell someone on my end I'm clearly going to sell that box if I'm in possession of it. This may lead to some confusion between both of our sites and inventory could get really messed up and confused. I have been making custom boxes now for about 7 years and if there is one thing that I have learned is not to disappoint people :slightly_smiling_face:

Is there anyway that you know of that could prevent this type of problem?"

Seems to me that one way to solve it would be if there's some way to link the sites so that when someone buys something from his website it disappears from our inventory, and vice versa. I'm not sure what platform he's using (here's the link: <https://www.aaroncaincustomboxes.com/online-store>) Is there a way to make that happen easily?
